              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Thermal neutron flux inducing  5E5 fission/minutes"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fast time of flight techniques are employed",
                " to study the neutron energy distribution from 0.3 to",
                " 5.0 Mev",
                "The experimentally determined fission neutron spectrum",
                " is expressed in the form: N(E)=(a0+a1E+a2E2)f(E),",
                " where E is the neutron energy in Mev, N(E) is the",
                " number of U233 fission neutrons per unit energy",
                " interval, f(E) is the U235 prompt fission neutron",
                " spectrum, and a0, a1, and a2 are constants normalized",
                " to give agreement with the known average number of",
                " U233 prompt fission neutrons"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PLATE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Proton recoil emulsions are utilized for",
                " neutron measurements from 1.2 to 7.0 Mev"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
